  "text": "(c) Gradual loss of endosymbiont genes There is little doubt that acquiring a bacterial endosymbiont and its subsequent transformation into a mitochondrion was a key event in the early evolutionary history of eukaryotes. How natural selection has favoured the maintenance of the symbiosis and the conversion of the endosymbiont to an organelle is hotly debated, and a number of scenarios that differ by the suggested metabolic nature of the endosymbiosis are being discussed [CITATION_1] .",
